						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vamsōddhārakanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara, •••rāyar, = c. 15th Century.</p>						

						<p>Beginning damaged. This records an asylum deed given to the ūravar of Peruṅgōḻiyūr (including both the western and eastern sections) in Teṉ-Panaṅgāḍu-nāḍu in Jayasiṅgakulakāla-vaḷanāḍu by two <hi rend="italic">araiyas</hi> of Pūkkuḍi in Vaḍamalai-nāḍu of Vaḍa-Panaṅgāḍu. For getting the necessary protection the <hi rend="italic">araiyas</hi> made a gift of land for offerings in the temple of Aḻagiya-kulōttuṅgar.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 765.]</p>						

						</summary>
